{"title": "Necro Cam", "content": "Once the detective has done The Summation and revealed the guilty party, we will get a Flashback of the crime being committed with the perpetrator completely visible, showing how they did it. This is particularly helpful if the murder method was fairly complicated, as a picture is of course worth a thousand words.\n\nSometimes there will be more than one flashback during the investigation as the detectives think out a theory; in this case, the theories and therefore the flashback may not even turn out to be correct. Sometimes it will be blurred with distorted sound and washed-out colors.\n\nCompare Once More, with Clarity! which repeats an earlier scene but adds new information which changes our perception of what went on in that moment. Nothing to do with Necromancy.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NecroCam", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheBoondockSaints", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheCaseOfTheCuriousBride", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/ErrolFlynn", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/FogOverFrisco", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Hero", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheLastOfSheila", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/CSI", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ColdCase", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StargateAtlantis", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Monk", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/JonathanCreek", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Psych", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/NewTricks", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/JonathanCreek", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/CrossingJordan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/House", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/TelevisionWithoutPity", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/MagicSchoolbus", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MurderSheWrote", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MurdochMysteries", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/AgathaChristie", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Justice", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Numb3rs", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/CriminalMinds", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StarTrekVoyager", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/VeronicaMars", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Vi